PORT ELIZABETH - Two young men had a lucky escape on Tuesday when they were forced to carry out an emergency landing in their light aircraft on a salt pan near Colchester, Eastern Cape police said. Eastern Cape police spokesperson Captain Andre Beetge said the two men sustained no injuries during the emergency landing. Beetge said the 19-year-old pilot of a Sling 2 aircraft experienced turbulence and had to land in a salt pan belonging to Tankatara Salt Works, close to Colchester. “Both himself and his 21-year-old male passenger were uninjured in the incident.” ALSO READ: WATCH: Pilot makes emergency landing on California freeway Beetge said the two-seater light aircraft belonged to a Port Elizabeth-based flying school and was still in the salt pan. He said the aircraft’s owners have since initiated a procedure to have the plane recovered. African News Agency/ANA